For sale by Private Treaty

CBRE are pleased to offer For Sale by Private Treaty a high profile mixed use freehold building in Sydney's premier inner west suburb - Balmain.

350-352 Darling Street, Balmain underwrites the opportunity for investors to 'de-risk' their investment through securing five independent tenancies under one title.

The building was extensively rebuilt in 1997 (DA 357/1997). The Leichhardt Council approved the construction of a 'new three storey building next to existing terrace, with new rear and upper storey addition to existing terrace'.

Key investment considerations;

* Prominent 'High Street' position in one of Sydney's premier harbour-side suburbs

* Main street exposure enjoying northern aspect

* Two retail tenancies - food use approved

* Middle level approved for restaurant / office

* Two residential apartments with district & harbour views

* Rear lane access providing on site parking

This building is available for immediate sale by private negotiation.
Please contact the exclusive selling agents for further information.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present to the market, for sale by public auction, this rare opportunity to purchase a prime medical investment property in the heart of Balmain.

This excellent strata investment property has recently been renovated to the highest standard with a newly exercised lease with secure annual increases. Positioned for success, the property is currently tenanted by “Clear Complexions” and would suit all investors looking to secure a solid and secure investment in the highly sought after Inner West.

Investment highlights include;

- Secure 5 +5 year lease to established medical tenant “Clear Complexions”
- Annual net passing income: $132,999^ with 5% annual increases
- 186sqm^ net lettable area with 2 car spaces
- Centrally located: moments from Balmain Town Centre
- Newly refurbished building with tenancy street frontage over 14m^

This property will be sold by way of public auction on Tuesday, 29th of August 2017 at 10:30am.
